OL,3,C'I wanted to help beat Hitler': 100-
OL,4,Cyear-old Windrush veteran
OL,6,FThe Windrush generation has come to
OL,7,Fsymbolise the first movement of mass
OL,8,Fmigration to the UK in the post-war
OL,9,Fera. The term takes its name from the
OL,10,FEmpire Windrush ship, which arrived at
OL,11,Fthe Port of Tilbury on 21 June 1948,
OL,12,Fcarrying hundreds of Caribbean
OL,13,Fmigrants, many of them veterans.
OL,15,FMr Ottey recalled the moment he
OL,16,Farrived in the UK to make Lincolnshire
OL,17,Fhis permanent home, when a stranger
OL,18,Fsingled him out.
OL,1,Woz5~k4{$z%~s1z5jw=hw1         G3/7
