OL,3,C'I wanted to help beat Hitler': 100-
OL,4,Cyear-old Windrush veteran
OL,6,F"He said 'hey mate, where you going?'.
OL,7,FI said 'I'm going up to Lincolnshire
OL,8,FI'm going to Boston'," Mr Ottey said.
OL,10,F"He said 'you don't want to go up
OL,11,Fthere mate, it's cold, even the
OL,12,Fsummer... so cold that people sleep
OL,13,Fwith the pigs to keep warm'."
OL,15,FMr Ottey settled with his wife Mavis
OL,16,Fand daughter Lesley, becoming a
OL,17,Fsuccessful accountant, local cricketer
OL,18,Fand an author.
