OL,3,C'I wanted to help beat Hitler': 100-
OL,4,Cyear-old Windrush veteran
OL,6,FBut in those early years, he said he
OL,7,Fwas met with some resistance and was
OL,8,Fshouted at in the street. He says he
OL,9,Fwas unaffected by the discrimination.
OL,11,F"It went in one ear and through the
OL,12,Fnext," he said.
OL,14,FThe Windrush Lincoln project also
OL,15,Ffeatures the story of renowned poet
OL,16,FBenjamin Zephaniah, who died on 7
OL,17,FDecember last year.
OL,1,Woz5~k4{$z%~s1z5jw=hw1         G5/7
